text.section:
The Office of Oral Health shall place priority on awarding grants to proposals that:
Are targeted to regions of the State where oral health services are most scarce for low-income, disabled, and Medicaid populations; and
Outline how the potential grantee will maximize limited resources, including:
Sharing of resources with other persons;
Case management to eliminate barriers to dental services;
Public-private purchasing agreements;
Obtaining matching funds to increase resources;
Incentives to increase provider participation;
Quantifiable outcome measures of success;
School-based screenings; and
Plans to ensure sustainability of services after termination of grants awarded under this subtitle.
